  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Isaiah 24:4",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 24:4",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The earth, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the land, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "mourneth and fadeth away ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "אבלה נבלה",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "abelah nabelah, lamenteth, falleth. The world languisheth,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " &c. — “The world,” says Bishop Lowth, “is the same with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the land; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that is, the kingdoms of Israel and Judah; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "orbis Iraeliticus,” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the Israelitish world. Heathen authors frequently speak of particular provinces and countries under the name of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "orbis, orbis habitabilis, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "orbis terrarum, the world, the habitable world, the whole world, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. And the same mode of speaking is often used in the Scriptures, where we not only find the Roman empire termed ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the world, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(even ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "all the world,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 2:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 11:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; but also Babylon, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 13:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) and this very land of Judea, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 12:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The haughty people of the land ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "מרום עם",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the height of the people, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "those of the highest dignity in it; or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the lofty people, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as Bishop Lowth renders it. Not only common people are depressed and stink in sorrow, but the magistrates and rulers, the rich and powerful, the haughty and high-minded. Indeed, these are wont to suffer most under such calamities, either as having most to lose, or as not being used to hardships.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
